1334void MipsAsmParser::
1335convertToMCInst(unsigned Kind, MCInst &Inst, unsigned Opcode,
1336 const OperandVector &Operands) {
1337 assert(Kind < CVT_NUM_SIGNATURES && "Invalid signature!");
1338 const uint8_t *Converter = ConversionTable[Kind];
1339 unsigned OpIdx;
1340 Inst.setOpcode(Opcode);
1341 for (const uint8_t *p = Converter; *p; p += 2) {
1342 OpIdx = *(p + 1);
1343 switch (*p) {
1344 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid conversion entry!");
1345 case CVT_Reg:
1346 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1347 break;
1348 case CVT_Tied: {
1349 assert(OpIdx < (size_t)(std::end(TiedAsmOperandTable) -
1350 std::begin(TiedAsmOperandTable)) &&
1351 "Tied operand not found");
1352 unsigned TiedResOpnd = TiedAsmOperandTable[OpIdx][0];
1353 if (TiedResOpnd != (uint8_t)-1)
1354 Inst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(TiedResOpnd));
1355 break;
1356 }
1357 case CVT_95_addGPR32AsmRegOperands:
1358 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addGPR32AsmRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1359 break;
1360 case CVT_95_addAFGR64AsmRegOperands:
1361 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addAFGR64AsmRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1362 break;
1363 case CVT_95_addFGR64AsmRegOperands:
1364 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addFGR64AsmRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1365 break;
1366 case CVT_95_addFGR32AsmRegOperands:
1367 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addFGR32AsmRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1368 break;
1369 case CVT_95_addSImmOperands_LT_32_GT_:
1370 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addSImmOperands<32>(Inst, 1);
1371 break;
1372 case CVT_95_addMSA128AsmRegOperands:
1373 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addMSA128AsmRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1374 break;
1375 case CVT_95_addSImmOperands_LT_16_GT_:
1376 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addSImmOperands<16>(Inst, 1);
1377 break;
1378 case CVT_95_Reg:
1379 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1380 break;
1381 case CVT_95_addImmOperands:
1382 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addImmOperands(Inst, 1);
1383 break;
1384 case CVT_95_addGPRMM16AsmRegOperands:
1385 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addGPRMM16AsmRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1386 break;
1387 case CVT_95_addConstantSImmOperands_LT_4_44__32_0_GT_:
1388 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addConstantSImmOperands<4, 0>(Inst, 1);
1389 break;
1390 case CVT_95_addConstantUImmOperands_LT_5_44__32_0_GT_:
1391 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addConstantUImmOperands<5, 0>(Inst, 1);
1392 break;
1393 case CVT_95_addConstantUImmOperands_LT_2_44__32_0_GT_:
1394 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addConstantUImmOperands<2, 0>(Inst, 1);
1395 break;
1396 case CVT_95_addUImmOperands_LT_16_GT_:
1397 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addUImmOperands<16>(Inst, 1);
1398 break;
1399 case CVT_95_addGPR64AsmRegOperands:
1400 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addGPR64AsmRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1401 break;
1402 case CVT_95_addConstantUImmOperands_LT_8_44__32_0_GT_:
1403 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addConstantUImmOperands<8, 0>(Inst, 1);
1404 break;
1405 case CVT_regZERO:
1406 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::ZERO));
1407 break;
1408 case CVT_95_addConstantUImmOperands_LT_5_44__32_32_44__32__MINUS_32_GT_:
1409 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addConstantUImmOperands<5, 32, -32>(Inst, 1);
1410 break;
1411 case CVT_regFCC0:
1412 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::FCC0));
1413 break;
1414 case CVT_95_addFCCAsmRegOperands:
1415 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addFCCAsmRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1416 break;
1417 case CVT_95_addCOP2AsmRegOperands:
1418 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addCOP2AsmRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1419 break;

1421 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addConstantUImmOperands<3, 0>(Inst, 1);
1422 break;

1431 break;

1433 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addConstantUImmOperands<10, 0>(Inst, 1);
1434 break;
1435 case CVT_95_addMemOperands:
1436 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addMemOperands(Inst, 2);
1437 break;
1438 case CVT_95_addConstantSImmOperands_LT_5_44__32_0_GT_:
1439 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addConstantSImmOperands<5, 0>(Inst, 1);
1440 break;
1441 case CVT_95_addCCRAsmRegOperands:
1442 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addCCRAsmRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1443 break;
1444 case CVT_95_addMSACtrlAsmRegOperands:
1445 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addMSACtrlAsmRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1446 break;
1447 case CVT_95_addConstantUImmOperands_LT_1_44__32_0_GT_:
1448 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addConstantUImmOperands<1, 0>(Inst, 1);
1449 break;
1450 case CVT_95_addConstantUImmOperands_LT_5_44__32_33_GT_:
1451 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addConstantUImmOperands<5, 33>(Inst, 1);
1452 break;
1453 case CVT_95_addConstantUImmOperands_LT_5_44__32_32_GT_:
1454 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addConstantUImmOperands<5, 32>(Inst, 1);
1455 break;
1456 case CVT_95_addConstantUImmOperands_LT_5_44__32_1_GT_:

1464 break;

1467 break;
1468 case CVT_95_addCOP0AsmRegOperands:
1469 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addCOP0AsmRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1470 break;
1471 case CVT_regZERO_64:
1472 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::ZERO_64));
1473 break;
1474 case CVT_95_addACC64DSPAsmRegOperands:
1475 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addACC64DSPAsmRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1476 break;
1477 case CVT_95_addConstantUImmOperands_LT_1_GT_:
1478 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addConstantUImmOperands<1>(Inst, 1);
1479 break;
1480 case CVT_regRA:
1481 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::RA));
1482 break;
1483 case CVT_regRA_64:
1484 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::RA_64));
1485 break;
1486 case CVT_95_addMicroMipsMemOperands:
1487 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addMicroMipsMemOperands(Inst, 2);
1488 break;
1489 case CVT_95_addCOP3AsmRegOperands:
1490 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addCOP3AsmRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1491 break;
1492 case CVT_95_addConstantSImmOperands_LT_10_44__32_0_GT_:
1493 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addConstantSImmOperands<10, 0>(Inst, 1);
1494 break;
1495 case CVT_95_addConstantUImmOperands_LT_32_GT_:
1496 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addConstantUImmOperands<32>(Inst, 1);
1497 break;
1498 case CVT_95_addStrictlyAFGR64AsmRegOperands:
1499 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addStrictlyAFGR64AsmRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1500 break;
1501 case CVT_95_addStrictlyFGR64AsmRegOperands:

1506 break;
1507 case CVT_95_addConstantUImmOperands_LT_7_44__32__MINUS_1_GT_:

1509 break;

1512 break;
1513 case CVT_ConvertXWPOperands:
1514 ConvertXWPOperands(Inst, Operands);
1515 break;
1516 case CVT_regAC0:
1517 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::AC0));
1518 break;
1519 case CVT_95_addGPRMM16AsmRegMovePPairFirstOperands:
1520 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addGPRMM16AsmRegMovePPairFirstOperands(Inst, 1);

1527 break;
1528 case CVT_95_addHI32DSPAsmRegOperands:

1530 break;
1531 case CVT_95_addLO32DSPAsmRegOperands:

1533 break;

1545 break;
1546 case CVT_95_addConstantUImmOperands_LT_20_44__32_0_GT_:
1547 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addConstantUImmOperands<20, 0>(Inst, 1);
1548 break;
1549 case CVT_95_addConstantSImmOperands_LT_6_44__32_0_GT_:
1550 static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addConstantSImmOperands<6, 0>(Inst, 1);
1551 break;
1552 case CVT_imm_95_2:
1553 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(2));
1554 break;
1555 case CVT_imm_95_6:
1556 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(6));
1557 break;
1558 case CVT_imm_95_4:

1563 break;
1564 case CVT_imm_95_31:
1565 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(31));
1566 break;
1567 }
1568 }

1570
1571void MipsAsmParser::
1572convertToMapAndConstraints(unsigned Kind,
1573 const OperandVector &Operands) {
1574 assert(Kind < CVT_NUM_SIGNATURES && "Invalid signature!");
1575 unsigned NumMCOperands = 0;
1576 const uint8_t *Converter = ConversionTable[Kind];
1577 for (const uint8_t *p = Converter; *p; p += 2) {
1578 switch (*p) {
1579 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid conversion entry!");
1580 case CVT_Reg:
1581 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
1582 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("r");
1583 ++NumMCOperands;
1584 break;
1585 case CVT_Tied:
1586 ++NumMCOperands;
1587 break;
1588 case CVT_95_addGPR32AsmRegOperands:
1589 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
1590 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
1591 NumMCOperands += 1;
1592 break;
1593 case CVT_95_addAFGR64AsmRegOperands:
1594 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
1595 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
1596 NumMCOperands += 1;
1597 break;
1598 case CVT_95_addFGR64AsmRegOperands:
1599 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
1600 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");

2114
2115static MatchClassKind matchTokenString(StringRef Name) {
2116 switch (Name.size()) {
2117 default: break;
2118 case 1: // 6 strings to match.
2119 switch (Name[0]) {
2120 default: break;
2121 case '#': // 1 string to match.
2122 return MCK__HASH_; // "#"
2123 case '(': // 1 string to match.
2124 return MCK__40_; // "("
2125 case ')': // 1 string to match.
2126 return MCK__41_; // ")"
2127 case '0': // 1 string to match.
2128 return MCK_0; // "0"
2129 case '[': // 1 string to match.
2130 return MCK__91_; // "["
2131 case ']': // 1 string to match.
2132 return MCK__93_; // "]"
2133 }
2134 break;
2135 case 2: // 1 string to match.
2136 if (memcmp(Name.data()+0, "16", 2) != 0)
2137 break;
2138 return MCK_16; // "16"
2139 case 3: // 1 string to match.
2140 if (memcmp(Name.data()+0, "bit", 3) != 0)
2141 break;
2142 return MCK_bit; // "bit"
2143 case 4: // 1 string to match.
2144 if (memcmp(Name.data()+0, "inst", 4) != 0)
2145 break;
2146 return MCK_inst; // "inst"
2147 }
2148 return InvalidMatchClass;
2149}

3463static unsigned validateOperandClass(MCParsedAsmOperand &GOp, MatchClassKind Kind) {
3464 MipsOperand &Operand = (MipsOperand &)GOp;
3465 if (Kind == InvalidMatchClass)
3466 return MCTargetAsmParser::Match_InvalidOperand;
3467
3468 if (Operand.isToken() && Kind <= MCK_LAST_TOKEN)
3469 return isSubclass(matchTokenString(Operand.getToken()), Kind) ?
3470 MCTargetAsmParser::Match_Success :
3471 MCTargetAsmParser::Match_InvalidOperand;
3472
3473 switch (Kind) {
3474 default: break;
3475 // 'ACC64DSPAsmReg' class
3476 case MCK_ACC64DSPAsmReg: {
3477 DiagnosticPredicate DP(Operand.isACCAsmReg());
3478 if (DP.isMatch())

4611#ifndef NDEBUG
4612const char *getMatchClassName(MatchClassKind Kind) {
4613 switch (Kind) {
4614 case InvalidMatchClass: return "InvalidMatchClass";
4615 case OptionalMatchClass: return "OptionalMatchClass";
4616 case MCK__HASH_: return "MCK__HASH_";

4622 case MCK__93_: return "MCK__93_";
4623 case MCK_bit: return "MCK_bit";
4624 case MCK_inst: return "MCK_inst";
4625 case MCK_Reg37: return "MCK_Reg37";
4626 case MCK_Reg19: return "MCK_Reg19";
4627 case MCK_ACC128: return "MCK_ACC128";
4628 case MCK_ACC64: return "MCK_ACC64";
4629 case MCK_CPURAReg: return "MCK_CPURAReg";
4630 case MCK_CPUSPReg: return "MCK_CPUSPReg";

4893
4894static bool checkAsmTiedOperandConstraints(const MipsAsmParser&AsmParser,
4895 unsigned Kind,
4896 const OperandVector &Operands,
4897 uint64_t &ErrorInfo) {
4898 assert(Kind < CVT_NUM_SIGNATURES && "Invalid signature!");
4899 const uint8_t *Converter = ConversionTable[Kind];
4900 for (const uint8_t *p = Converter; *p; p += 2) {
4901 switch (*p) {
4902 case CVT_Tied: {
4903 unsigned OpIdx = *(p + 1);
4904 assert(OpIdx < (size_t)(std::end(TiedAsmOperandTable) -
4905 std::begin(TiedAsmOperandTable)) &&
4906 "Tied operand not found");
4907 unsigned OpndNum1 = TiedAsmOperandTable[OpIdx][1];
4908 unsigned OpndNum2 = TiedAsmOperandTable[OpIdx][2];
4909 if (OpndNum1 != OpndNum2) {
4910 auto &SrcOp1 = Operands[OpndNum1];
4911 auto &SrcOp2 = Operands[OpndNum2];
4912 if (SrcOp1->isReg() && SrcOp2->isReg()) {
4913 if (!AsmParser.regsEqual(*SrcOp1, *SrcOp2)) {
4914 ErrorInfo = OpndNum2;
4915 return false;
4916 }
4917 }
4918 }
4919 break;
4920 }
4921 default:
4922 break;
4923 }
4924 }
4925 return true;
4926}

5430 }

5433 }
5434 };

8123
8124#include "llvm/Support/Debug.h"
8125#include "llvm/Support/Format.h"
8126
8127unsigned MipsAsmParser::
8128MatchInstructionImpl(const OperandVector &Operands,
8129 MCInst &Inst,
8130 uint64_t &ErrorInfo,
8131 FeatureBitset &MissingFeatures,
8132 bool matchingInlineAsm, unsigned VariantID) {
8133 // Eliminate obvious mismatches.
8134 if (Operands.size() > 9) {
8135 ErrorInfo = 9;
8136 return Match_InvalidOperand;
8137 }
8138
8139 // Get the current feature set.
8140 const FeatureBitset &AvailableFeatures = getAvailableFeatures();
8141
8142 // Get the instruction mnemonic, which is the first token.
8143 StringRef Mnemonic = ((MipsOperand &)*Operands[0]).getToken();
8144
8145 // Some state to try to produce better error messages.
8146 bool HadMatchOtherThanFeatures = false;
8147 bool HadMatchOtherThanPredicate = false;
8148 unsigned RetCode = Match_InvalidOperand;
8149 MissingFeatures.set();
8150 // Set ErrorInfo to the operand that mismatches if it is
8151 // wrong for all instances of the instruction.
8152 ErrorInfo = ~0ULL;
8153 // Find the appropriate table for this asm variant.
8154 const MatchEntry *Start, *End;
8155 switch (VariantID) {
8156 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid variant!");
8157 case 0: Start = std::begin(MatchTable0); End = std::end(MatchTable0); break;
8158 }
8159 // Search the table.
8160 auto MnemonicRange = std::equal_range(Start, End, Mnemonic, LessOpcode());
8161
8162 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "AsmMatcher: found " <<
8163 std::distance(MnemonicRange.first, MnemonicRange.second) <<
8164 " encodings with mnemonic '" << Mnemonic << "'\n");
8165
8166 // Return a more specific error code if no mnemonics match.
8167 if (MnemonicRange.first == MnemonicRange.second)
8168 return Match_MnemonicFail;
8169
8170 for (const MatchEntry *it = MnemonicRange.first, *ie = MnemonicRange.second;
8171 it != ie; ++it) {
8172 const FeatureBitset &RequiredFeatures = FeatureBitsets[it->RequiredFeaturesIdx];
8173 bool HasRequiredFeatures =
8174 (AvailableFeatures & RequiredFeatures) == RequiredFeatures;
8175 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "Trying to match opcode "
8176 << MII.getName(it->Opcode) << "\n");
8177 // equal_range guarantees that instruction mnemonic matches.
8178 assert(Mnemonic == it->getMnemonic());
8179 bool OperandsValid = true;
8180 for (unsigned FormalIdx = 0, ActualIdx = 1; FormalIdx != 8; ++FormalIdx) {
8181 auto Formal = static_cast<MatchClassKind>(it->Classes[FormalIdx]);
8182 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher",
8183 dbgs() << " Matching formal operand class " << getMatchClassName(Formal)
8184 << " against actual operand at index " << ActualIdx);
8185 if (ActualIdx < Operands.size())
8186 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << " (";
8187 Operands[ActualIdx]->print(dbgs()); dbgs() << "): ");
8188 else
8189 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << ": ");
8190 if (ActualIdx >= Operands.size()) {
8191 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "actual operand index out of range ");
8192 OperandsValid = (Formal == InvalidMatchClass) || isSubclass(Formal, OptionalMatchClass);
8193 if (!OperandsValid) ErrorInfo = ActualIdx;
8194 break;
8195 }
8196 MCParsedAsmOperand &Actual = *Operands[ActualIdx];
8197 unsigned Diag = validateOperandClass(Actual, Formal);
8198 if (Diag == Match_Success) {
8199 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher",
8200 dbgs() << "match success using generic matcher\n");
8201 ++ActualIdx;
8202 continue;
8203 }
8204 // If the generic handler indicates an invalid operand
8205 // failure, check for a special case.
8206 if (Diag != Match_Success) {
8207 unsigned TargetDiag = validateTargetOperandClass(Actual, Formal);
8208 if (TargetDiag == Match_Success) {
8209 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher",
8210 dbgs() << "match success using target matcher\n");
8211 ++ActualIdx;
8212 continue;
8213 }
8214 // If the target matcher returned a specific error code use
8215 // that, else use the one from the generic matcher.
8216 if (TargetDiag != Match_InvalidOperand && HasRequiredFeatures)
8217 Diag = TargetDiag;
8218 }
8219 // If current formal operand wasn't matched and it is optional
8220 // then try to match next formal operand
8221 if (Diag == Match_InvalidOperand && isSubclass(Formal, OptionalMatchClass)) {
8222 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "ignoring optional operand\n");
8223 continue;
8224 }
8225 // If this operand is broken for all of the instances of this
8226 // mnemonic, keep track of it so we can report loc info.
8227 // If we already had a match that only failed due to a
8228 // target predicate, that diagnostic is preferred.
8229 if (!HadMatchOtherThanPredicate &&
8230 (it == MnemonicRange.first || ErrorInfo <= ActualIdx)) {
8231 if (HasRequiredFeatures && (ErrorInfo != ActualIdx || Diag != Match_InvalidOperand))
8232 RetCode = Diag;
8233 ErrorInfo = ActualIdx;
8234 }
8235 // Otherwise, just reject this instance of the mnemonic.
8236 OperandsValid = false;
8237 break;
8238 }
8239
8240 if (!OperandsValid) {
8241 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "Opcode result: multiple "
8242 "operand mismatches, ignoring "
8243 "this opcode\n");
8244 continue;
8245 }
8246 if (!HasRequiredFeatures) {
8247 HadMatchOtherThanFeatures = true;
8248 FeatureBitset NewMissingFeatures = RequiredFeatures & ~AvailableFeatures;
8249 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "Missing target features:";
8250 for (unsigned I = 0, E = NewMissingFeatures.size(); I != E; ++I)
8251 if (NewMissingFeatures[I])
8252 dbgs() << ' ' << I;
8253 dbgs() << "\n");
8254 if (NewMissingFeatures.count() <=
8255 MissingFeatures.count())
8256 MissingFeatures = NewMissingFeatures;
8257 continue;
8258 }
8259
8260 Inst.clear();
8261
8262 Inst.setOpcode(it->Opcode);
8263 // We have a potential match but have not rendered the operands.
8264 // Check the target predicate to handle any context sensitive
8265 // constraints.
8266 // For example, Ties that are referenced multiple times must be
8267 // checked here to ensure the input is the same for each match
8268 // constraints. If we leave it any later the ties will have been
8269 // canonicalized
8270 unsigned MatchResult;
8271 if ((MatchResult = checkEarlyTargetMatchPredicate(Inst, Operands)) != Match_Success) {
8272 Inst.clear();
8273 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(
8274 "asm-matcher",
8275 dbgs() << "Early target match predicate failed with diag code "
8276 << MatchResult << "\n");
8277 RetCode = MatchResult;
8278 HadMatchOtherThanPredicate = true;
8279 continue;
8280 }
8281
8282 if (matchingInlineAsm) {
8283 convertToMapAndConstraints(it->ConvertFn, Operands);
8284 if (!checkAsmTiedOperandConstraints(*this, it->ConvertFn, Operands, ErrorInfo))
8285 return Match_InvalidTiedOperand;
8286
8287 return Match_Success;
8288 }
8289
8290 // We have selected a definite instruction, convert the parsed
8291 // operands into the appropriate MCInst.
8292 convertToMCInst(it->ConvertFn, Inst, it->Opcode, Operands);
8293
8294 // We have a potential match. Check the target predicate to
8295 // handle any context sensitive constraints.
8296 if ((MatchResult = checkTargetMatchPredicate(Inst)) != Match_Success) {
8297 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher",
8298 dbgs() << "Target match predicate failed with diag code "
8299 << MatchResult << "\n");
8300 Inst.clear();
8301 RetCode = MatchResult;
8302 HadMatchOtherThanPredicate = true;
8303 continue;
8304 }
8305
8306 if (!checkAsmTiedOperandConstraints(*this, it->ConvertFn, Operands, ErrorInfo))
8307 return Match_InvalidTiedOperand;
8308
8309 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(
8310 "asm-matcher",
8311 dbgs() << "Opcode result: complete match, selecting this opcode\n");
8312 return Match_Success;
8313 }
8314
8315 // Okay, we had no match. Try to return a useful error code.
8316 if (HadMatchOtherThanPredicate || !HadMatchOtherThanFeatures)
8317 return RetCode;
8318
8319 ErrorInfo = 0;
8320 return Match_MissingFeature;
8321}
8322
8323namespace {
8324 struct OperandMatchEntry {
8325 uint16_t Mnemonic;
8326 uint8_t OperandMask;
8327 uint8_t Class;
8328 uint8_t RequiredFeaturesIdx;
8329
8330 StringRef getMnemonic() const {
8331 return StringRef(MnemonicTable + Mnemonic + 1,
8332 MnemonicTable[Mnemonic]);
8333 }
8334 };
8335
8336 // Predicate for searching for an opcode.
8337 struct LessOpcodeOperand {
8338 bool operator()(const OperandMatchEntry &LHS, StringRef RHS) {
8339 return LHS.getMnemonic() < RHS;
8340 }
8341 bool operator()(StringRef LHS, const OperandMatchEntry &RHS) {
8342 return LHS < RHS.getMnemonic();
8343 }
8344 bool operator()(const OperandMatchEntry &LHS, const OperandMatchEntry &RHS) {
8345 return LHS.getMnemonic() < RHS.getMnemonic();
8346 }
8347 };
8348} // end anonymous namespace

11663OperandMatchResultTy MipsAsmParser::
11664tryCustomParseOperand(OperandVector &Operands,
11665 unsigned MCK) {
11666
11667 switch(MCK) {
11668 case MCK_ACC64DSPAsmReg:
11669 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11670 case MCK_AFGR64AsmReg:
11671 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11672 case MCK_CCRAsmReg:
11673 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11674 case MCK_COP0AsmReg:
11675 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11676 case MCK_COP2AsmReg:
11677 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11678 case MCK_COP3AsmReg:
11679 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11680 case MCK_FCCAsmReg:
11681 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11682 case MCK_FGR32AsmReg:
11683 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11684 case MCK_FGR64AsmReg:
11685 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11686 case MCK_GPR32AsmReg:
11687 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11688 case MCK_GPR32NonZeroAsmReg:
11689 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11690 case MCK_GPR32ZeroAsmReg:
11691 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11692 case MCK_GPR64AsmReg:
11693 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11694 case MCK_GPRMM16AsmReg:
11695 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11696 case MCK_GPRMM16AsmRegMoveP:
11697 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11698 case MCK_GPRMM16AsmRegMovePPairFirst:
11699 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11700 case MCK_GPRMM16AsmRegMovePPairSecond:
11701 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11702 case MCK_GPRMM16AsmRegZero:
11703 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11704 case MCK_HI32DSPAsmReg:
11705 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11706 case MCK_HWRegsAsmReg:
11707 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11708 case MCK_LO32DSPAsmReg:
11709 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11710 case MCK_MSA128AsmReg:
11711 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11712 case MCK_MSACtrlAsmReg:
11713 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11714 case MCK_MicroMipsMemGP:
11715 return parseMemOperand(Operands);
11716 case MCK_MicroMipsMem:
11717 return parseMemOperand(Operands);
11718 case MCK_MicroMipsMemSP:
11719 return parseMemOperand(Operands);
11720 case MCK_InvNum:
11721 return parseInvNum(Operands);
11722 case MCK_JumpTarget:
11723 return parseJumpTarget(Operands);
11724 case MCK_MemOffsetSimmPtr:
11725 return parseMemOperand(Operands);
11726 case MCK_MemOffsetUimm4:
11727 return parseMemOperand(Operands);
11728 case MCK_MemOffsetSimm9_0:
11729 return parseMemOperand(Operands);
11730 case MCK_MemOffsetSimm10_0:
11731 return parseMemOperand(Operands);
11732 case MCK_MemOffsetSimm11_0:
11733 return parseMemOperand(Operands);
11734 case MCK_MemOffsetSimm12_0:
11735 return parseMemOperand(Operands);
11736 case MCK_MemOffsetSimm16_0:
11737 return parseMemOperand(Operands);
11738 case MCK_MemOffsetSimm10_1:
11739 return parseMemOperand(Operands);
11740 case MCK_MemOffsetSimm10_2:
11741 return parseMemOperand(Operands);
11742 case MCK_MemOffsetSimm10_3:
11743 return parseMemOperand(Operands);
11744 case MCK_Mem:
11745 return parseMemOperand(Operands);
11746 case MCK_RegList16:
11747 return parseRegisterList(Operands);
11748 case MCK_RegList:
11749 return parseRegisterList(Operands);
11750 case MCK_StrictlyAFGR64AsmReg:
11751 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11752 case MCK_StrictlyFGR32AsmReg:
11753 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11754 case MCK_StrictlyFGR64AsmReg:
11755 return parseAnyRegister(Operands);
11756 default:
11757 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
11758 }
11759 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
11760}
11761
11762OperandMatchResultTy MipsAsmParser::
11763MatchOperandParserImpl(OperandVector &Operands,
11764 StringRef Mnemonic,
11765 bool ParseForAllFeatures) {
11766 // Get the current feature set.
11767 const FeatureBitset &AvailableFeatures = getAvailableFeatures();
11768
11769 // Get the next operand index.
11770 unsigned NextOpNum = Operands.size() - 1;
11771 // Search the table.
11772 auto MnemonicRange =
11773 std::equal_range(std::begin(OperandMatchTable), std::end(OperandMatchTable),
11774 Mnemonic, LessOpcodeOperand());
11775
11776 if (MnemonicRange.first == MnemonicRange.second)
11777 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
11778
11779 for (const OperandMatchEntry *it = MnemonicRange.first,
11780 *ie = MnemonicRange.second; it != ie; ++it) {
11781 // equal_range guarantees that instruction mnemonic matches.
11782 assert(Mnemonic == it->getMnemonic());
11783
11784 // check if the available features match
11785 const FeatureBitset &RequiredFeatures = FeatureBitsets[it->RequiredFeaturesIdx];
11786 if (!ParseForAllFeatures && (AvailableFeatures & RequiredFeatures) != RequiredFeatures)
11787 continue;
11788
11789 // check if the operand in question has a custom parser.
11790 if (!(it->OperandMask & (1 << NextOpNum)))
11791 continue;
11792
11793 // call custom parse method to handle the operand
11794 OperandMatchResultTy Result = tryCustomParseOperand(Operands, it->Class);
11795 if (Result != MatchOperand_NoMatch)
11796 return Result;
11797 }
11798
11799 // Okay, we had no match.
11800 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
11801}

11803#endif // GET_MATCHER_IMPLEMENTATION

11806#ifdef GET_MNEMONIC_SPELL_CHECKER
11807#undef GET_MNEMONIC_SPELL_CHECKER
11808
11809static std::string MipsMnemonicSpellCheck(StringRef S, const FeatureBitset &FBS, unsigned VariantID) {
11810 const unsigned MaxEditDist = 2;
11811 std::vector<StringRef> Candidates;
11812 StringRef Prev = "";
11813
11814 // Find the appropriate table for this asm variant.
11815 const MatchEntry *Start, *End;
11816 switch (VariantID) {
11817 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid variant!");
11818 case 0: Start = std::begin(MatchTable0); End = std::end(MatchTable0); break;
11819 }
11820
11821 for (auto I = Start; I < End; I++) {
11822 // Ignore unsupported instructions.
11823 const FeatureBitset &RequiredFeatures = FeatureBitsets[I->RequiredFeaturesIdx];
11824 if ((FBS & RequiredFeatures) != RequiredFeatures)
11825 continue;
11826
11827 StringRef T = I->getMnemonic();
11828 // Avoid recomputing the edit distance for the same string.
11829 if (T.equals(Prev))
11830 continue;
11831
11832 Prev = T;
11833 unsigned Dist = S.edit_distance(T, false, MaxEditDist);
11834 if (Dist <= MaxEditDist)
11835 Candidates.push_back(T);
11836 }
11837
11838 if (Candidates.empty())
11839 return "";
11840
11841 std::string Res = ", did you mean: ";
11842 unsigned i = 0;
11843 for (; i < Candidates.size() - 1; i++)
11844 Res += Candidates[i].str() + ", ";
11845 return Res + Candidates[i].str() + "?";
11846}
11847
11848#endif // GET_MNEMONIC_SPELL_CHECKER

11851#ifdef GET_MNEMONIC_CHECKER
11852#undef GET_MNEMONIC_CHECKER
11853
11854static bool MipsCheckMnemonic(StringRef Mnemonic,
11855 const FeatureBitset &AvailableFeatures,
11856 unsigned VariantID) {
11857 // Find the appropriate table for this asm variant.
11858 const MatchEntry *Start, *End;
11859 switch (VariantID) {
11860 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid variant!");
11861 case 0: Start = std::begin(MatchTable0); End = std::end(MatchTable0); break;
11862 }
11863
11864 // Search the table.
11865 auto MnemonicRange = std::equal_range(Start, End, Mnemonic, LessOpcode());
11866
11867 if (MnemonicRange.first == MnemonicRange.second)
11868 return false;
11869
11870 for (const MatchEntry *it = MnemonicRange.first, *ie = MnemonicRange.second;
11871 it != ie; ++it) {
11872 const FeatureBitset &RequiredFeatures =
11873 FeatureBitsets[it->RequiredFeaturesIdx];
11874 if ((AvailableFeatures & RequiredFeatures) == RequiredFeatures)
11875 return true;
11876 }
11877 return false;
11878}
